X'=\begin{pmatrix}   x'(t)\\   y'(t) \end{pmatrix}
 \left\{         \begin{array}{ll}             x'(t)=\color{blue}{0}\cdot x(t)+\color{red}{1}\cdot y(t)\\             y'(t)=\color{red}{1}\cdot x(t)+\color{blue}{0}\cdot y(t)         \end{array}     \right.
X'(t)=A~X(t)
A=\begin{pmatrix}   \color{blue}{0} & \color{red}{1} \\   \color{red}{1} & \color{blue}{0}\\   \end{pmatrix}
